      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RINGBARK LARRY (1) was sent out at odds but pinged the lids and never headed leading all the way to score by 0.8 lengths (29.92) at this track in Grade 5 over 520m. Solid record at the distance winning two races. The form out of his last race has been franked. Expected to be right there at the finish again. MUSTANG HAYZE (2) showed good speed off a low draw but weakened and run over late when 7th over 520m at this track in Free For All company. Has a good record here at this journey. The form out of last race has been strong. Key runner who gets her chance to atone. EXTREME TENSION (4) is worth forgiving for his last effort when fourth (30.46) at this track over 520m. Solid record here at the distance winning seven races. Cannot be taken lightly. COMICAL WARREN (5) boasts a solid strike-rate over this trip.",
